						<summary>

						<p>On the east wall of the first <hi rend="italic">prākāra</hi> in the Māśilāmaṇīśvara temple.</p>						

						<p>Rājēndrachōḷa I. Year 3: 1014-15 A.D.</p>						

						<p>This inscription records the gift of 90 sheep left in the hands of some shepherds by Nāgaṉ Veḷḷi of Ugumbil, in Māṅgāḍu-nāḍu, a district of Puliyūr-kōṭṭam, a division of Jayaṅgoṇḍachōḷa maṇḍapam, for burning a perpetual lamp daily in the temple of Tirumullaivāyil-āṇḍār, at Tirumullaivāyil in Kāṉappēṟ[ūr]-nāḍu, a district of Puḻaṟ-kōṭṭam.</p>						

						</summary>
